sjc.analysis

Class ReachingDefinitionAnalysis

  • java.lang.Object
    • sjc.analysis.MonotonicDataFlowFramework<Pair<java.lang.String,ASTNode>>
      • sjc.analysis.ReachingDefinitionAnalysis

  • public class ReachingDefinitionAnalysis
extends MonotonicDataFlowFramework<Pair<java.lang.String,ASTNode>>
    An instance of MonotonicDataFlowFramework to compute reaching definition. The lattice element of this analysis is a Pair of String which represents a field, a parameter, or a local variable name, and FieldDeclaration, SingleVariableDeclaration, Assignment (in ExpressionStatement), respectively, which indicates the last definition of the variable (i.e., a field or a method parameter declaration is considered as the field or the parameter initial definition).
    Author:
    Robby
